                        <p dbid="657ae1eba789759594df0807"><![CDATA[<strong>Energy</strong> is measured in joules (J). Joules measure the unit of energy.]]></p>
                        <p element_imported="0.2" dbid="657ae1eba789759594df0808"><![CDATA[<strong>Power</strong> is measured in watts, where 1 watt (W) is a rate corresponding to one joule per second.]]></p>
                        <p element_imported="0.2" dbid="657ae1eba789759594df0809"><![CDATA[<strong>A kilowatt (kW)</strong> is, therefore, also a rate corresponding to 1000 joules per second.]]></p>
                        <p element_imported="0.2" dbid="657ae1eba789759594df080a"><![CDATA[<strong>A kilowatt-hour (kWh)</strong> is a measure of energy (J) corresponding to one kilowatt of power sustained for one hour.]]></p>
